<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK Honor Guards Likely to Lose Bearskin Hats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The British Ministry of Defense
is considering to use synthetic alternatives to replace the honor
guards' bearskin hats made from the Canadian brown bearskin.
</P>
<P>
Britain's Defense Minister for defense procurement John Gilbert
has urged the army to look at synthetic replacements for the
present headgear, known as the busby, according British defense
sources.
</P>
<P>
However, synthetic fake fur could prove to be a disaster. An
army spokesman said, "When the (synthetic) hats are dry, they
attract a great deal of static electricity."
</P>
<P>
"In the rain they look like a lady might look when she steps
out of the shower. Synthetics don't imitate long-haired animal
furs well," he said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported nearly 3,000 British soldiers from five
regiments such as the Grenadier, Scots and Welsh Guards have worn
busbies since the battle of Waterloo in 1815. 
</P>
</TEXT>
