<HEADLINE> 12 Injured in Austrian Rail Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Twelve people were injured in
Austria today when a passenger train ran into a goods train at a
railway station in the Ybbstal valley of the Lower Austria State.
</P>
<P>
Two people among the injured were in grave condition.
</P>
<P>
The collision happened early this morning when the passenger
train went onto a rail track occupied by a stationary goods train.
</P>
<P>
A local radio station said that the cause of the accident might
have been the wrong dispatching of trains. 
</P>
</TEXT>
