<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK's Unemployment Total Lowest for 17 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The jobless total in Britain fell
again last month to its lowest figure since 1980, according to the
latest figures released here today.
</P>
<P>
The number out of work and claiming benefit was down 49,800 to
1,550,000 in July -- 5.5 percent of the workforce and a larger cut
than many economists in the City had expected.
</P>
<P>
It was the 17th consecutive monthly fall in the
seasonally-adjusted total.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, official figures showed average earnings rose by
4.25 percent in the year to June, unchanged from the previous
month.
</P>
<P>
Education and Employment Minister Baroness Blackstone welcomed
the latest fall in the jobless total. But she warned that youth
unemployment still presented a danger.
</P>
<P>
The government's welfare-to-work scheme designed to get 250,000
under-25s off benefit and into jobs would be the key in keeping
unemployment down, she added.
</P>
<P>
The new deal, funded by the windfall tax from privatized public
sectors, would provide skills and experience for young people to
find jobs, she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
