<HEADLINE> Bulgarian International Master to Compete in Chess Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- International master Vesselin
Topalov of Bulgaria was invited to take part in the coming FIDE
world championship, according to local reports.
</P>
<P>
The other Bulgarian entry is Kiril Georgiev, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Sixty-eight elite chess masters will take part in the first
round of comeptition slated for December 8-25 in Groeningen, the
Netherlands. The 34 first-round winners will be joined by another
32 higher-ranked players among whom are Vesselin Topalov and Kiril
Georgiev.
</P>
<P>
Vesselin Topalov shares the fourth place in the world rankings
with FIDE's world champion Anatoly Karpov of Russia with Georgiev
in the 13th place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
