<HEADLINE> Shares Tumble on Bull Unloading at BSE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 13 (Xinhua)-- Share prices tumbled down on
the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market today on heavy bull
unloading and bear pressure from speculators.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said activity was low and was mostly
speculators-driven, as major players remained sidelined.
</P>
<P>
Reflecting the market trend, the BSE 30-scrip sensitive index
opened higher at 4,419.34 but closed at 4,370.13, a fall of 54.90
points from the previous close of 4,425.03.
</P>
<P>
The national index also dropped by 23.22 points to close at
1,900.55. The BSE-200 closed lower at 424.47 and the US dollar
index at 197.79 from the last close of 428.63 and 199.78
respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
