<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Host Southern African Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Wastewater management and water
pollution by the farming and industrial sectors will feature
predominantly in the Second Southern African Water and Wastewater
Conference here next month.
</P>
<P>
The five-day meeting to begin on September 15, will be
attended by representatives from the government, the private
sector and local authorities.
</P>
<P>
Under the theme of "Water: Guarding Resources Against Drought
and Pollution", locals are expected to present papers on several
water related issues including water quality, the development of
institutions and human resources to ensure water security, the
overview of rural water supply and management of pollution on
surface and groundwater by mining activities, said a draft
program released here today.
</P>
<P>
"Papers will draw on past experience to analyse current
practices and stimulate debate concerning probable future
directions for the sector," noted the draft program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
