<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya, Jordan to Sign Trade Pact </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan and Jordanian
governments will soon sign an agreement to strengthen their
currently low two-way trade despite years of cordial relations.
</P>
<P>
The trade balance now is tilted in favor of Kenya which
imported goods worth 22,000 U.S. Dollars last year from Jordan
and exported 2.2 million Dollars to the kingdom, said an
organizer of a Jordan trade fair here today.
</P>
<P>
The imports to Kenya from Jordan are mainly medicines,
phosphates and a few manufactured products. Kenya sold Jordan
coffee, fresh fruits, vegetables and fish.
</P>
<P>
A total of 25 Jordanian companies are exhibiting over 90
products, including carpets, paper products and kitchen utensils
here. The show started on Monday and is to end on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
