<HEADLINE> Liberia Shortens Curfew to Three Hours </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The new Liberian government
announced today that it has shortened a night-time curfew that
has been in place since 1992 to three hours.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here quoted Liberian Justice Minister Peter
Jallah as saying that the curfew, which was from midnight till
dawn, will now be enforced from 2:00 A.M. to 5:00 A.M..
</P>
