<HEADLINE> Tajik Officials Deny Fightings in South </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Tajik Deputy Interior Minister
Abdusattor Radzhabov and the commander of a rapid response
brigade, Colonel Sukhrob Kasymov, categorically denied today that
armed clashes are continuing in Kurgan Tyube and the Gisar valley
as some reports said.
</P>
<P>
The Itar-Tass news agency reported from Dushanbe, capital of
Tajikistan, that Radzhabov said there has been no fighting since
this morning and the situation remains calm. Kasymov's troops have
under control together with presidential guards the entire highway
south of Dushanbe down to Kurgan Tyube and the Gisar valley.
</P>
<P>
The two officials also denied that Tajik President Emomali
Rakhmonov met with Colonel Makhmud Khudoiberdyev, commander of an
elite brigade, at one of the Russian military units earlier today.
</P>
<P>
They said that Khudoiberdyev has stepped down and is expected
to attend the surrender of weapons by its brigade Thursday
morning.
</P>
<P>
However, the opposition defense council of Tajikistan's central
and southern regions, which has been recognized by the Tajik
government as anti-constitutional, has disagreed with Rakhmonov's
decision to sack Khudoiberdyev.
</P>
<P>
The Itar-Tass quoted Kasim Babayev, deputy head of the Kurgan
Tyube regional administration and a member of the defense council,
as saying that the decision was taken after the brigade insisted
that Khudoiberdyev stay.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it said Rakhmonov has signed a decree on some
measures to stabilize the military and political situation in the
republic.
</P>
<P>
The decree gives all citizens who illegally possess weapons
three days to turn them in to authorities. If they do that by
midnight August 16, they will be exempt from criminal
responsibility.
</P>
<P>
The president also ordered the Interior Ministry to remove all
illegal roadblocks and checkpoints by 9:00 Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The decree establishes a state commission for the acceptance of
weapons, ammunition and special property of Khudoiberdyev's
brigade.
</P>
<P>
Report said that the Tajik authorities have asked the command
of the Commonwealth of Independent States peacekeeping troops in
Tajikistan and personally Lieutenant-General Boris Dyukov to
assist the newly established commission in the performance of its
duties. 
</P>
