<HEADLINE> 11 Hikers Missing in Flash Flood in Arizona </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Eleven hikers were missing
today in a flash flood that sent an 11-foot wall of water roaring
through a normally dry canyon in north-central Arizona, an
Associated Press report said.
</P>
<P>
A helicopter spotted one body about two kilometers downstream
from where the hikers were swept away and a tour guide leading a
group of the hikers was rescued while clinging to a rock at the
bottom of Antelope Canyon near Lake Powell in north-central
Arizona near the Utah line.
</P>
<P>
Among those who were missing were three French adults, one
British national and some Swedish nationals, the report said.
</P>
<P>
It was the fourth devastating flash flood in Arizona in a week
during the Southwest's annual monsoon season.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, a wall of water rushed down Cataract Canyon on the
Havasupai Indian Reservation near the Grand Canyon, and hundreds
of residents and tourists had to be rescued by helicopter.
</P>
</TEXT>
