<HEADLINE> Computer Language Processors to Meet in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong University of
Science and Technology and Qinghua University in Beijing will
jointly hold a conference of language processing for computers
here on August 20.
</P>
<P>
The conference, the 5th Workshop on Very Large Corpora, which
is held for the first time in Asia, will bring together
international experts in computational linguistics focusing on
research in Chinese language.
</P>
<P>
Dekai Wu, local organizer of the Workshop at the Hong Kong
University of Science and Technology, said that the very different
 structure and script of the Chinese language provide extra
challenges to computational linguists.
</P>
<P>
He said that as the world increasingly communicates online,
this research will help information to cross language borders, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The conference will present recent breakthroughs in techniques
from statistics, pattern recognition and machine learning to help
break the so-called "artificial intelligence bottleneck" by
extracting knowledge from corpora automatically.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
