<HEADLINE> Five Die of Diseases in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 14 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of encephalitis
and meningitis has claimed five lives in Jhapa district of eastern
Nepal, the official RSS news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The dead were among the 33 patients admitted to the local
hospital since May 1, which included 21 Nepalese and 12 Bhutanese
refugees, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
About 100,000 Bhutanese refugees have been staying in eight
UN-camps in eastern Nepal after being forced to flee Bhutan in
1989 and early 1990s.  
</P>
