<HEADLINE> Australia Pleased with Human Rights Talks with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Australian Foreign Minister
Alexander Downer said tonight he was pleased with the first round
of talks with China on human rights.
</P>
<P>
"The dialogue marks a substantial and very welcome development
in our relationship with China," the foreign minister was quoted
by the Australian Associated Press as saying.
</P>
<P>
The consultations reflected the commitment of both sides to
moving the relationship forward, he said.
</P>
<P>
"I look forward to continuing to work with China to advance the
promotion and protection of human rights," Downer said.
</P>
<P>
Australia and China tonight wrapped up their first round of
high level talks on human rights in Beijing.  
</P>
