<HEADLINE> French Court Tries Skinhead for Murder </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 14 (Xinhua) -- A court in Paris today put on
trial a skinhead charged with murdering a Moroccan by pushing him
into the Seine River in central Paris in May 1995.
</P>
<P>
Michael Freminet, 21, was charged with murder by pushing Brahim
Bouarram, 29, into the river where he drowned.
</P>
<P>
The attack took place after the extreme-right National Front
held a demonstration in the area.
</P>
<P>
Freminet could face 30 years in jail under the criminal code of
France.
</P>
<P>
Three other people, who were with Freminet during the attack
but did not push Bouarram, were charged with "non-assistance to a
person in danger."
</P>
<P>
The attack was widely condemned in France and former President
Francois Mitterrand himself threw a spray of flowers into the
Seine River where Bouarram was drowned. 
</P>
