<HEADLINE> Burning Drugs In East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Authorities in China's Fujian
Province today destroyed narcotic drugs and announced some
penalties for drug dealers at a rally in Fuqing City.
</P>
<P>
Public security officers have destroyed 8,300 grams of heroin,
3,200 grams of opium, and 88,800 grams of "ice". Officials also
announced that 20 drug dealers were arrested.
</P>
<P>
According to the officials, public security officers have
cracked down on drug crimes, and the province's first drug
rehabilitation center was established in the city.
</P>
<P>
The city's public security officers have dealt with 21 drugs
cases and have arrested 41 people in the first seven months of
this year. There are also 1,217 drugs abusers registered in the
city.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government chose Fuqing City for the rally
because it is the family home of Lin Zexu, a Chinese hero who
burnt opium supplies in 1839. 
</P>
