<HEADLINE> Housing Project Benefits Poor Families in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's Comfort Housing
Project which provides inexpensive housing to low and middle
income families is reaping success.
</P>
<P>
According to urban construction authorities, the 1.88 million
sq.m. of housing far constructed has enabled 21,000 Beijing
families move into their new homes since 1993.
</P>
<P>
Most of families previously lived in dilapidated housing or had
per capita living space of less than four square meters.
</P>
<P>
The city plans to build another two million square meters of low
cost housing over the next three years to provide new housing for
50,000 families with per capita living space less than four square
meters.
</P>
<P>
The capital's current per capita living space stands at eight
square meters.  
</P>
