<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Volume Up in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The import and export volume
of south China's Guangdong Province for the first seven months of
this year was 64.55 billion US dollars, according to the
provincial foreign trade department.
</P>
<P>
Exports for the period totaled 39.3 billion US dollars, up 31
percent from the same period last year, with a favorable trade
balance of 14.8 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Officials say the rapid growth comes from the soft landing of
the Chinese economy, the growing world market, and restructuring
of the province's foreign trade companies.
</P>
<P>
Exports from the province's Maoming and Qingyuan cities
increased 200 percent, and those of Meizhou, Shanwei and Jieyang
were up 100 percent, compared with the same period last year. The
export volume of the cities of Guangzhou and Shantou also
surpassed the provincials average. 
</P>
