<HEADLINE> HK Air Cargo Throughput Takes Another Leap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's monthly Air Cargo
throughput totals have breached 1996 records for the seventh
consecutive month, according to Hong Kong Air Cargo Terminals
Limited (HACTL) today.
</P>
<P>
The air cargo throughput for July amounted to 144,369 tons,
representing a 15.4 percent increase over the corresponding month
last year.
</P>
<P>
Overall, export cargo totaled 69,091 tons, up 19 percent on
July 1996; import cargo amounted to 58,145 tons, up 10.9 percent
and transshipment goods came to 17,134 tons, up 17.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
For the first seven months of this year, HACTL handled more
than 923,829 tons of air cargo, representing a 16.5 percent growth
on the corresponding period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
HACTL expects to reach the one-million-ton milestone figure by
mid-August. 
</P>
