<HEADLINE> Cambodian Leader Declares Close Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian First Prime
Minister Ung Huot said here today that the top leaders of the
country will cooperate closely with each other to maintain
political stability and develop the country's economy.
</P>
<P>
Ung Huot made the remarks at the Phnom Penh international
airport this afternoon after returning from Beijing where he and
his delegation met Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk who is under
medical treatment in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
The delegation also included Cambodian Second Prime Minister
Hun Sen and Acting Head of State Chea Sim.
</P>
<P>
The delegation briefed Sihanouk on the latest situation in
Cambodia, Ung Huot said. He said the king showed satisfaction over
the restoration of law and order in the country.
</P>
<P>
"During the five-hour-long talks, Hun Sen, Chea Sim and I
promised to comply with the king's wish to cooperate with each
other closely," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen said all Cambodian people need King Norodom Sihanouk.
</P>
<P>
"We must adhere to the constitutional monarchy and fight
against anybody who seeks to overthrow such system," he added.
</P>
<P>
On the fate of the ousted former First Prime Minister Prince
Norodom Ranariddh, Hun Sen said that Ranariddh "must be brought to
trial as he violated the laws."
</P>
<P>
"It is meaningless for the ASEAN to persuade the Phnom Penh
government to hold informal talks with Ranariddh," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Ranariddh was ousted after heavy fighting between troops loyal
to him and Hun Sen in early July. Ung Huot was then nominated by
Ranariddh's royalist FUNCINPEC party as the new first prime
minister and his nomination was approved by the parliament and the
acting head of state, Chea Sim.
</P>
<P>
The top-level Cambodian delegation including Ung Huot, Hun Sen
and Chea Sim started its visit to China on Monday and met with
Chinese Premier Li Peng and Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian
Qichen on Wednesday. 
</P>
