The Interfax news agency reported that Russia had mediated in
arranging the meeting between Rakhmonov and Khudoiberdyev, which
was held Wednesday near Dushanbe, capital of Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
The military conflict occurred on August 9 in southwest of
Tajikistan between the supporters of Col. Sukhrob Kasymov,
commander of a special-purpose brigade of the Tajik Interior
Ministry and those of Customs Committee Chairman Yakub Salimov.
</P>
<P>
The situation deteriorated when Khudoiberdyev, commander of a
presidential rapid reaction brigade was involved in the conflict
in an effort to support the units of Salimov.
</P>
<P>
Belov praised both sides for signing the agreement. He said
that although the future was unpredictable in the country, the
government and the opposition had seen the necessity of preventing
new military confrontation in Tajikistan. 
