<HEADLINE> Presidential, Vice-Presidential Bill Passed in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 14 (XINHUA) -- The two Houses of Parliament
in India have unanimously approved the Presidential,
Vice-Presidential Bill with the Upper House passing it here today
without discussion.
</P>
<P>
The Bill which seeks to discourage frivolous candidate from
filing nominations to the offices of President and Vice-President,
was passed by the Lower House of Parliament Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
The Presidential and Vice-Presidential Elections (second
amendment) Bill 1997 provides for enhancing the security deposit
to 15,000 rupees (422.54 U.S. dollars) and increasing the minimum
number of proposers and seconders to 50 each in Presidential
nomination and 20 each for Vice- Presidential nomination.
</P>
