<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Implementation of Scientific Progress Law Inspected (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A recent report by the State Science and Technology
Commission shows that promulgation of the Law on Scientific and
Technological Progress has enabled China to introduce successful
and effective practices in advancing its scientific and
technological system reform in conjunction with economic
restructuring.
</P>
<P>
The technology market has emerged as an important market for
essential production factors, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The number of technological contracts for 1996 reached 220,000,
with the total turnover of 30 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Some 600 research institutes now serve as major technological
developers for enterprises, while another 500 institutions have
joined some form of cooperation with enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The industrial output value of the country's 52 national-level
development zones for hi-tech industries hit 210 billion yuan in
1996. The zones earned 2.9 billion US dollars in foreign
exchange from exports and generated 17.6 billion yuan in profits
and taxes.
</P>
<P>
The over 50,000 hi-tech non-state-run enterprises established
as a result of the reform have developed into a major force in the
country's economic development.
</P>
<P>
The report points out that technological development in
agriculture, animal husbandry and fisheries contributed greatly to
this year's good grain harvest and increased meat production last
year.
</P>
<P>
It indicates that China has recorded remarkable progress in
basic scientific research and hi-tech development.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, China became the first country in the world to draft
the national-level 21st Century Agenda, a document which has since
gained worldwide cooperation and drawn the attention of the
governments at all levels and Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
The report notes that the country's expenditures in scientific
and technological research and development have increased on an
annual basis, but still fall short of the high rate of economic
growth.
</P>
<P>
The country spent a total of 116.6 billion yuan on scientific
and technological development in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970814.0106 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Top Palestinian Legislator on Peace Talks With </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 14 (Xinhua) -- A top Palestinian legislator said
today that the Palestinians have no objection to entering talks
with Israel on a final peace deal if the interim peace accords are
carried out simultaneously.
</P>
<P>
"The Palestinians are not against final-settlement talks but
the final status talks must run parallel to the implementation of
all agreements reached during the transitional period,"
legislative Palestinian Council (PC) Speaker Ahmed Queria told the
Egyptian Voice of Arabs radio.
</P>
<P>
"The Palestinian problem must be dealt with and solved as a
whole package. Otherwise the conflict would never be settled," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians have agreed to resume security coordination
with Israel with the help of the United States, Queria said,
hoping that in return "Israel and the U.S. would respond to the
Palestinian demands."
</P>
<P>
Queria made the statement as U.S. Mideast Coordinator Dennis
Ross wound up his four-day shuttle trip to Israel and the
Palestinian National Authority, bringing what he called "a new
beginning" in restoring security cooperation between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
His mission will pave way for the visit to the region by
U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright, who is expected to
take a major initiative that reportedly would address some kind of
freeze of Israeli settlement expansion and an acceleration of
talks on a final peace settlement.
</P>
<P>
Queria told the Arabic radio that the Palestinians discussed
with Ross the reasons that led to the present tension in the peace
process, atop of which "Israel's disrespect of agreements and the
continuation of Jewish settlement activities."
</P>
<P>
He said that Ross heard the Palestinian viewpoint and told the
Palestinians that his mission is only limited to restoring
confidence and resuming security coordination between the Israelis
and Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Queria expressed the hope that Albright's upcoming tour would
reassert the principle of trading land for peace and the return of
Palestinian rights.
</P>
<P>
Peace talks and security coordination between Israel and the
PNA stopped in March when Israel began to build a housing project
for Jews in East Jerusalem. Resumption of the talks were disrupted
again as two bombing attacks hit Jerusalem on July 30, killing 15
people and wounding 170 others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
