<HEADLINE> 27 PKK Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-seven rebels of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in military
operations staged by the Turkish security forces in southeastern
Turkey, an official statement said today.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule said that the security forces killed the 27 rebels in the
operations in Incebel Mountains near Beytussebap town of Sirnak
province bordering northern Iraq. However, it failed to disclose
when the PKK rebels were killed in the region.
</P>
<P>
One soldier of the security forces was also killed and six
others, including one village guard, were wounded in the armed
clashes with the PKK guerrillas in Sirnak, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
It added that the security forces captured one PKK militant
and three PKK members surrendered to the security forces in
southeastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 13-year-old separatist war for
autonomy, which has claimed over 27,000 lives in eastern and
southeastern Turkey since August 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
