<HEADLINE> Food Expo '97 Opens in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Food Expo '97, an event
featuring mouthwatering delicacies from all over the world, was
kicked off today in Hong Kong, a metropolitan renowned for varied
cuisine.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony of Food Expo '97, Mrs. Lessie
Wei, director of agriculture and fisheries, said that Food Expo is
possibly the most important annual event in Hong Kong for the food
industry.
</P>
<P>
"The event has been successfully held for a number of years,
attracting a large number of exhibitors and visitors, both local
and overseas," she said.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Hong Kong Trade Development Council (TDC),
Food Expo '97 is running at the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center through August 18.
</P>
<P>
This year the food exposition attracts more than 170 local and
overseas companies to present an extensive array of products from
traditional and regional delicacies, specialty drinks to kitchen
utensils.
</P>
<P>
For the first time, the "Snack Parade" has been specially set
up to let consumers know more about different kinds of snacks
through exciting games including "Guessing Game" and "Snack Smart
Quiz".
</P>
<P>
With a population of 6.3 million, Hong Kong is certainly a big
market for food products. Last year, Hong Kong's imports of food
and beverages reached 58 billion HK dollars (7.4 billion US
dollars), a four-percent rise over 1995, according to TDC
Executive Director Michael Sze, who was also speaking at the
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"World-renowned for fine cuisine, Hong Kong is backed up by a
strong catering industry. With one eating place for about every
650 people, Hong Kong may well have the world's highest ratio of
restaurants and cafes," he said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's processed food and beverages industry has continued
 to flourish, with last year's total exports amounting at 26.2
billion HK dollars (3.4 billion US dollars), up 9 percent over
1995. Major markets include the Chinese mainland, Japan and the
United States. 
</P>
