<HEADLINE> HK's External Trade Up in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's re-export value in
 June this year increased by 10 percent over a year earlier to
101.1 billion HK dollars (13 billion U.S. dollars), according to
the figures released by the Census and Statistics Department
today.
</P>
<P>
The value of domestic exports in the month rose by 5.9 percent
to 17.9 billion HK dollars (2.3 billion U.S. dollars), while
imports increased by 6.4 percent to 131.7 billion HK dollars (17
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Comparing the first half of 1997 with the same period of 1996,
the value of Hong Kong's re-exports increased by 4.4 percent to
575.1 billion HK dollars (74.2 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The value of domestic exports in the first half of 1997
decreased by 3.4 percent over the same period in 1996 to 95.9
billion HK dollars (12.37 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The value of imports in the first half of 1997, at 767.5
billion HK dollars (99 billion U.S. dollars), increased by 4.6
percent over the same period in 1996. 
</P>
