<HEADLINE> HongkongBank Opens New Branch Premises in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Hongkong and Shanghai
Banking Corporation Limited today opened its new premises in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Christopher Langley, general manager of HongkongBank, said that
it is an auspicious occasion, noting that it is the first official
event for the bank on the Chinese mainland since Hong Kong's
return to its motherland with the establishment of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
The opening of the Beijing premises is the third such event for
HongkongBank on the Chinese mainland in recent months. In June
the bank opened new premises in Pudong, Shanghai and in Dalian in
northeast China.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Branch of the bank, with 54 staff, offers a wide
range of foreign exchange banking services including
deposit-taking, loans, guarantees, trade finance and project
finance.
</P>
<P>
According to Langley, the branch is equipped with advanced
computer systems and satellite linkages to all HongkongBank
branches on the mainland and its headquarters in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
In December 1996, HongkongBank was one of the first overseas
banks to obtain approval from the People's Bank of China to
conduct Renminbi business in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
HongkongBank has seven branches on the Chinese mainland,
including the new premises in Beijing, Dalian and Pudong. It also
has branches in Qingdao, Shenzhen, Tianjin and Xiamen and
representative offices in Chengdu, Guangzhou and Wuhan. 
</P>
