</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 184.87 million units, worth
586.46 million Singapore dollars (about 388.38 million U.S.
dollars). Advances overtook declines by 175 to 138, while 298
other counters stayed steady.
</P>
<P>
Local software maker Summit was the most actively traded stock
as it registered a turnover of 25.32 million units. It was
followed by Hotung which had 14.69 million shares traded. CM Tel
was next with 11.73 million shares changed hands.
