<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belgian Biplane Crash Caused by Human Error: Inquiry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Belgian aviation authorities
have attributed to human error the July 26 acrobatics plane crash
at Ostend, the Free Belgium daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted Transportation Minister Michel Daerden as
saying that the crash, which killed 10 people and injured 56
others, was not caused by technical failure.
</P>
<P>
The minister pronounced Wednesday the preliminary results of an
investigation by aviation specialists along with designers and
manufacturers of the German-made Falcon XT300 biplane.
</P>
<P>
The specialists concluded after analyzing video recordings of
the lethal flight that the plane was at a height of only 10 to 15
meters from the ground after the pilot, Captain Amr Hani Bilal of
the Jordanian Royal Falcon Squadron, did almost a vertical drive
following his last of a series of loops.
</P>
<P>
It was impossible to pull up the plane again at such a height.
</P>
<P>
The plane then crashed onto a first-aid tent at the edge of the
spectator area, spraying debris and burning kerosene on to
spectators.
</P>
<P>
The crash was the first fatal accident of the Ostend air show,
which has been held five times.
</P>
<P>
Belgian aviation and military authorities have called off all
ensuing acrobatic flights scheduled for the next few months
pending the conclusive results of the investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970814.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Retain Tight Monetary Policy (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- China's financial sector has
witnessed continuing stability this year, and the central bank
will adhere to the moderately tight monetary policy to help
facilitate sustained, rapid and healthy national economic
development.
</P>
<P>
Dai Xianglong, governor of the People's Bank of China, the
country's central bank, made the assertions at a press conference
here today.
</P>
<P>
"The financial sector has remained fully committed to pursuing
a moderately tight monetary policy, safeguarding and mitigating
financial risks, and supporting economic structural adjustments,"
Dai said.
</P>
<P>
China's money supply has increased appropriately this year,
according to the central bank governor.
</P>
<P>
He noted that broad money (M2), the combination of cash in
circulation and all types of deposits, rose by 34.4 percent in
1994 and 25.3 percent in 1996.
</P>
<P>
However, the value of M2 approached 8,345 billion yuan (about
1,000 billion US dollars) at the end of July, a year-on-year rise
of 18.1 percent and a 7.2 percentage point drop on ending figures
for last year.
</P>
<P>
The value of narrow money (M1), the combination of cash in
circulation plus the demand deposits of enterprises, grew to 3,110
billion yuan by the end of last month, up 18.4 percent on July
1996 figures and equal to levels at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Currency in circulation fell to 10.9 percent of M2 by the end
of June, down from 19.8 percent in 1994, according to Dai.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970814.0135 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Retain Tight Monetary Policy (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dai said that increased lending has basically met this year's
requirements for China's continued economic development.
</P>
<P>
The outstanding loan balance for all financial institutions
reached 6,870 billion yuan by the end of July, up 450.3 billion
yuan from the beginning of this year. However, actual growth fell
by 15.6 billion yuan on last year's same period, according to Dai.
</P>
<P>
Of the total lending, 287.8 billion yuan was loaned by the
state-owned banks, 24.6 billion yuan less than a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Combined deposits for all financial institutions totaled 7,610
billion yuan by the end of July, with enterprise deposits rising
by 26.6 percent on the previous year's period to 2,573.3 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The marked growth in enterprise deposits indicates the
strengthened overall payment capability of enterprises, said Dai.
</P>
<P>
He added that other signs of financial stability center on the
fact that the central bank has appropriately controlled base
money, and money market transaction has remained steady throughout
the year.
</P>
<P>
The value of base money, a major indicator of the money supply,
reached 2,750 billion yuan by the end of July, a year-on-year rise
of 18.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Dai noted that increased foreign exchange holdings resulted in
an additional 175.4 billion yuan of liquidity by the end of July,
a substantial 33.5 billion yuan rise on the same 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
The central bank recalled 107 billion yuan in loans from
financial institutions during the first seven months of the year,
up 63.7 billion yuan on the same 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
Dai told reporters that the ratio of standby liquidity of
commercial banks was 7.7 percent at the end of July, a rate he
said indicates a sufficient payment capability of banks.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970814.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Retain Tight Monetary Policy (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China's foreign exchange reserves continued to expand during
the first seven months, reaching 126 billion US dollars by the end
of July, up 21 billion US dollars from the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate for Chinese currency, the Renminbi (RMB)
yuan, has largely remained stable at 8.29 against the US dollar
this year.
</P>
<P>
"The real exchange rate of the RMB has experienced a certain
range of appreciation due to the country's falling prices," said
Dai.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that China's financial sector continues to face
various problems and difficulties.
</P>
<P>
State banks must still deal with problems related to increasing
overdue loans and decreasing interest collections which have
resulted from the excessively high debt ratios of the state-owned
enterprises (SOE) and the increasing losses suffered by some SOEs,
as well as poor bank management, Dai noted.
</P>
<P>
Wholly state-owned banks had an unrealized interest rate income
of 143.1 billion yuan due on overdue loans by the end of June, up
24.6 billion yuan on the beginning of this year, he said.
</P>
<P>
Dai said that idle production capacity can be attributed to the
inability of outdated industrial and product structures and the
inability of older enterprises to adapt to the market demand
changes in the course of economic restructuring, as well as to
redundant construction in recent years.
</P>
<P>
He noted that it will be impossible to solve related problems
by relaxing overall economic controls and stressed that related
efforts must focus on deepening enterprise reform and accelerating
the pace of economic restructuring.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970814.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Korea to Parole 360 Prisoners to Mark Liberation Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The South Korean government will
