<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- Eight people were killed and 24 wounded when a bus crashed
with a truck in Landes, southwestern France. All the victims were
members of a Portuguese folk song band on their way back to
Portugal from Belgium.
</P>
<P>
-- After three years of fleeing and extremely weak, the last
group of some 2,500 Rwandan Hutu refugees in former Zaire are
waiting to be repatriated to Rwanda. Many of them are dying of
weakness and diseases despite the efforts by non-governmental
organizations to help them.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- From now on until 2020, the population of southern France,
mainly Provence-Alpes-Cote-d'Azur, Rhone-Alpes and the Corsica,
will increase while the population in the north, east and central
parts of the country will decrease, says a Direction of Population
and Migration study. The Paris region will also see its population
increasing during that period.
</P>
<P>
-- French automakers benefited from the strong U.S. dollar in
the past year as it helped them in increasing exports. Three big
brands of French cars, Renault, PSA and Michelin, have all seen a
6.3-10 percent increase in sales. The major markets are Britain,
Spain and Italy, whose currencies stood firm against the dollar.
</P>
