<HEADLINE> Steel Giant Attracts Overseas Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Handan Iron and Steel Group, a
major Chinese steel producer in north China's Hebei Province, will
receive a loan of 230 million German marks from an international
banking syndicate.
</P>
<P>
The company has signed related agreements with the Bank of
China (BOC) and the banking syndicate headed by the Germany's
Frankfort Branch of Barclays Bank Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The agreements call for the syndicate to loan 230 million marks
to the BOC which will then deliver the money to the company.
</P>
<P>
Handan will use the loan to purchase advanced production
equipment from Germany.
</P>
<P>
According to bank officials, "The Handan Group received
favorable terms for the two-part loan -- export credit and
commercial loans.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of China is the nation's only bank engaged in
international banking business activities. BOC has borrowed a
total of 19 billion US dollars from overseas banks over the past
few years to support development of the country's key industrial
projects.  
</P>
