<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Yunnan, a mountainous frontier
province in southwest China, has drafted an ambitious plan to
provide all local villages with access to highways, telephones and
electricity by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
