<HEADLINE> Tightening Control on Audio-Visual Market in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Culture Department of
northwest China's Qinghai province seized more than 9,200 illegal
copies of audio and visual products during the first seven months
of this year.
</P>
<P>
The products were found in 529 units that were selling pirated
or pornographic cassettes, video tapes, and VCDs.
</P>
<P>
