<HEADLINE> Awareness Program on Constitutional Reform Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
launched a drive aimed at promoting awareness of constitutional
reform among the people in the north and east, a senior official
said today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news briefing, Minister of Justice,
Constitutional Affairs, Ethnic Affairs and National Integration G.
L. Peiris said the program has been launched by the government
recently.
</P>
<P>
He said awareness meetings were organized with the
participation of civilian groups, which included school teachers,
government officials, farmers, members of the fishing community
and representatives of citizens' committees.
</P>
<P>
A total of 13 such meetings were held in Jaffna Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The participants were invited to raise questions and concerns
regarding the constitutional reform process with particular
reference to the devolution of power, said the minister.
</P>
<P>
He added that the program will be continued in other cleared
areas of the north and east together with ongoing evaluation of
the effectiveness of the initial phase.
</P>
<P>
The government has been conducting the constitutional reform
which seeks to devolve part of the authority of the central
government with a view to solving the complex ethnic problem since
1995.  
</P>
