<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Encourages Overseas Branches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, recently issued regulations allowing
profitable private enterprises to open overseas subsidiaries.
</P>
<P>
The regulations stipulate that all registered private
enterprises in Guangzhou will be allowed to open solely funded,
joint venture, cooperative or shareholding overseas subsidiaries
so long as the new enterprises import advanced equipment and
scarce raw materials or products, and earn foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou trade centers throughout the world and overseas
agencies in the city will provide them with all necessary
conveniences, including accommodations and offices.
</P>
<P>
Those wishing to explore overseas market by exporting products
abroad will be required to complete all customs procedures and
obtain foreign exchange through approved trade centers.
</P>
<P>
Authorized private firms abroad will be under the management as
other local Chinese-funded enterprises and will receive assistance
from relevant Chinese embassies when facing difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Private overseas companies investing in their parent companies
or other enterprises in Guangzhou will enjoy the same preferential
government treatment granted to foreign companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
