<HEADLINE> S. African Armed Forces to Be All Volunteers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 14 (Xinhua) -- S. African National
Defense Force (SANDF) will be an all-volunteer force and there
will be no conscription, a local daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Citizen quoted Deputy Defense Minister Ronnie Kasrils as
saying the SANDF would be an all-volunteer force and that there
would consequently be no liability to render military service for
conscripts who served in the armed forces prior to the first
non-racial general elections in april 1994.
</P>
<P>
However, Kasrils said, during a state of emergency or a state
of national defense declared in terms of the constitution if
their services were required, all current and future volunteers
in the SANDF would be liable to be called up after completion of
their term of service.
</P>
<P>
A new act would provide that personnel that are liable to do
additional service but refuse to do so on grounds of conscience,
would be entitled to render alternative non-military services,
Kasrils said. 
</P>
