<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan
Province, a rapidly developing province, has used a massive influx
of government funding to build new schools in poor counties.
</P>
<P>
The province has built 1,440 schools in 34 poverty-stricken
counties over the past two years.
</P>
<P>
The Provincial government plans to open another 940 schools
over the next few years, according to Yuan Guorui, director of the
Provincial Education Commission.
