<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Chinese Treatment for Leukemia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have shown
that realgar, a traditional Chinese herbal medicine that has been
used for hundreds of years, is effective in treating an acute form
of leukemia.
</P>
<P>
Realgar is a mineral containing arsenic disulfides and is used
as a detoxicant and parasiticide.
</P>
<P>
Lu Daopei, a professor at Beijing Medical University's People's
Hospital, said during a recent Beijing medical symposium attended
by experts and scholars from China and the Republic of Korea that
his research group has been doing research on the deadly disease
with realgar since December, 1994, and 32 patients with acute
promyelocytic leukemia did not suffer a relapse after taking
realgar orally for a period of time.
</P>
<P>
The patients are mostly between the ages of 30 and 40, and the
eldest is 61.
</P>
<P>
None of them took any other anti-leukemia medicine during the
treatment.
</P>
<P>
In the past, Lu said, patients of the disease were given bone
marrow transplants, and although the success rate was as high as
80 percent, it was very difficult for doctors to find suitable
bone marrow for patients.
</P>
<P>
He said his research has shown that the survival rate from
taking oral realgar is the highest of all treatments, and his
hospital has taken to using oral realgar as the first choice in
treating this form of leukemia.
</P>
<P>
Lu Daopei is China's pioneer of bone marrow transplants in
treating leukemia, and he has helped establish Asia's largest bone
marrow transplant center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
