<HEADLINE> United States Wins Admiral's Cup After 28 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The United States won for the
first time since 1969 on Wednesday by defeating defending champion
Italy on the Admiral's Cup at Cowes, Isle of Wight, Britain.
</P>
<P>
Italy seemed to repeat the way it overtook the United States
two years ago for the title as its "Madina Milano" crossed first
ahead of "Flash Gordon 3" of the United States in the 974-km
Fastnet race, the final event of the nine-race regatta.
</P>
<P>
The turnaround occurred when Italy's "Brava Q8", which looked
certain to finish first in the ILC 40 class, was suddenly dropped
by a wind.
</P>
<P>
American John Kolius' "MK Cafe" took the chance to catch up and
finished second behind Germany's mid-boat "Pinta" with Italy at
sixth.
</P>
<P>
The victory of Kolius and his crew insured the slim lead for
the Americans and helped them revenge Italy.
</P>
<P>
Italy dropped to third overall in the Admiral's Cup, with
Germany moving up to second. The fourth to seventh places were
Australia, Britain, New Zealand and Scandinavia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
