<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The government approved a
total of 47-billion-U.S.-dollar state budget for 1998 Wednesday
night, reported the state-run Israel Radio today.
</P>
<P>
The budget, including a 660-million-dollar cut in public
spending, was approved by a vote 9-3 with 2 abstentions.
</P>
<P>
The radio said those opposed were Education Minister Zevulun
Hammer, Labor and Social Affairs Minister Eli Ishai and Transport
Minister Yitzhak Levy. Foreign Minister David Levy and Interior
Minister Eli Suissa abstained.
</P>
