Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai, who was fighting for
additional funds for the military, walked out of the meeting.
Trade and Industry Minister Natan Shalansky did not attend the
meeting, but said that he did so for personnel reasons.
</P>
<P>
Finance Minister Ya'akov Neeman's plan for economic reforms
was approved unanimously. The Ministers also agreed on an
inflation target of 7-10 percent.
</P>
<P>
The budget will be submitted to Knesset (parliament) for
approval when it resumes after summer recess. 
