<HEADLINE> Central Bank Governor Predicts Ten-Percent Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- China's economic growth rate is
expected to approach ten percent this year with the inflation rate
kept under four percent, predicted Dai Xianglong, the central bank
head, at a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
Dai went on to say that the Chinese economy will continue to
grow at eight percent annually over the next two or three years,
and an inflation rate of below five percent is also attainable.
</P>
<P>
"There are difficulties and risks in our country's economic and
financial work, but we believe that China will be able to maintain
high economic growth in tandem with low inflation," the central
bank governor said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
