<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Electric Generator Manufacturers Get Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Power equipment manufacturers in
northeast China have obtained 700 million yuan in loans to help
produce big hydropower generators for the Three Gorges Dam on the
middle reaches of the Yangtze River, "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The State Development Bank of China (SDB) recently signed
contracts over the loan issue with the Harbin Power equipment
Co. Ltd (HPEC) and its holder Harbin Power Plant Equipment Group
Corp in Harbin, capital of Heilongjiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The loans include a 13-year 580 million yuan commercial loans
and a 9-year 120 million yuan low-interest loan.
</P>
<P>
HPEC, one of the country's leading producers for large
hydropower equipment, will use SDB's loans to upgrade and expand
its production sites and facilities, and to improve its products
according to the international standards.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Dam Project, the world's largest dam project,
needs 26 electric generating units, each with a capacity of over
700,000 kilowatts, of which 14 will be manufactured by Chinese
companies. The rest 12 generators will involve international
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
HPEC expects to double its production capacity through the
renovation and expansion. Its annual production capacity for large
hydropower generators will be increased from the current 800,000
kilowatts to 1.6 million kilowatts on completion of the expansion
project.
</P>
<P>
Through cooperation with other companies, HPEC will provide two
generators for the Three Gorges Dam before 2003. The Three Gorges
Dam is scheduled to start power generation in 2003 and is expected
to be finished in 2009, requiring a total investment of 200
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
SDB, the largest and most important of China's three policy
banks set up in 1994, is designed to support the nation's
construction of infrastructure, basic and pillar industries. So
far, it has provided the Three Gorges Dam project with a financial
help worth 30 billion yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
