<HEADLINE> ICBC Shanghai Branch Bank Increases Credits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 14 (Xinhua/OANA) -- The Shanghai branch of the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC), the country's
largest bank, is expected to increase its line of credits by 10
billion yuan (1.2 billion US dollars) in the second half of this
year.
</P>
<P>
According to the ICBC branch, the main recipients of the loans
include 39 large state-owned enterprises for which ICBC Shanghai
is the sponsoring bank.
</P>
<P>
The branch noted that financial backing will be strengthened
for the municipality's six pillar industries, the enterprises with
the State holding a controlling stake and the enterprises in
foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The amount of loans for science and technology undertakings and
for housing will also increase, the bank said.
</P>
<P>
It cited the second phase project of the Waigaoqiao Power
Plant, the Pudong International Airport and some other leading
construction projects as the key targets of the new loans.  
</P>
