<HEADLINE> Thailand, Myanmar to Open Border Friendship Bridge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Thailand and Myanmar Friday will
officially inaugurate a friendship bridge linking Thailand's Mae
Sot and Myanmar's Myawaddy, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The opening of the highway bridge will add a link in the
ambitious Asian highway construction plan project which aims to
forge road links from Afghanistan to Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The bridge was jointly built by Thailand and Myanmar with a
funding assistance of 350 million baht (14 million U.S. dollars)
from Australia.
</P>
<P>
Thailand has also invested 79.2 million baht (3.2 million
dollars) for the construction of the bridge.  
</P>
