<HEADLINE> USAID Aid For Sri Lanka's Jaffna Technical College </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The United States Agency for
International Development (USAID) and the United Nations
Development Programme (UNDP) have jointly granted over 517,000 US
dollars to rehabilitate Sri Lanka's Jaffna Technical College.
</P>
<P>
The grant will be used to replace machine tools in the
Engineering Craft Training Division and the Engineering Technical
Division in the college, according to local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Jaffna Technical College was established in 1959 and has
been a very active and well regarded public institution.
</P>
<P>
The college regularly receives over 6,000 applications with
about 12 percent of these applications being accepted.
</P>
<P>
In October 1995 the total number of students was 1,100 with 600
full-time and 500 part-time students.
</P>
<P>
The college lost most of its equipment during the most recent
round of the ethnic war although the buildings remains largely
intact.
</P>
<P>
The Sri Lanka government will participate in the project by
facilitating appropriate clearances for supplies and personnel
from Colombo, the reports said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
