<DOCNO> XIE19970814.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Contribute One Billion US Dollars of Aid to Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- China has decided to contribute
one billion US dollars to an international package to help
Thailand overcome its current financial crisis, Dai Xianglong,
governor of the People's Bank of China (PBC), said here today.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference here this morning, Dai said his bank has
notified the International Monetary Fund (IMF) and the central
bank of Thailand of the decision, which he said is supported by
the Chinese Government.
</P>
<P>
The governor also said that China will attend the related
meetings for the specific arrangements of the international
package loans to Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Dai expressed his confidence in the ability of the
Thai government to tide over its present financial difficulties
and adjust its economy with the help of the IMF and the financial
circles of Asian countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
