<DOCNO> XIE19970814.0227 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Revises Fuel Prices for Bus Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar Ministry of Energy
has revised fuel prices to enable bus services to buy freely the
required amount of fuel as a measure to tackle the passenger
transport problem.
</P>
<P>
The New Light of Myanmar today quoted Chairman of the Yangon
Division Law and Order Restoration Council and Commander Maj. Gen.
Khin Maung Than as saying that the government's revision of fuel
prices is to control the fuel price gap.
</P>
<P>
Previously, the prices of petrol and diesel oil per gallon
(4.546 liters) prescribed by the state were 25 Kyats (about 12
U.S. cents according to market exchange rate) and 20 Kyats (10
U.S. cents) respectively, while those in the open market were
about 280 Kyats (1.4 dollars) and 220 Kyats (1.1 dollars).
</P>
<P>
The revised state-prescribed fuel prices were 180 Kyats (90
U.S. cents) and 120 Kyats (60 U.S. cents) per gallon for petrol
and diesel respectively.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting here Wednesday, the commander said that
the bus fares have also been revised reasonably to help bus owners
make up for higher fuel prices.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar's state-run Road Transport undertook transportation of
passengers and goods with 1,025 passenger buses, 140 taxis and
2,106 haulage trucks and the cooperative transport services had
been operating with 387 passenger buses and 423 haulage trucks.
</P>
<P>
According to the 1996-97 data, registration for private-owned
vehicles comprised 178,252 passenger cars and 36,183 haulage
trucks showing an increase of 18,210 passenger buses and 4,385
haulage trucks over the previous year's .
</P>
<P>
According to official sources, Myanmar imported annually nearly
100 million dollars worth of fuel oil in the last nine years to
meet local consumption, up from about 20 million dollars annually
in the past.
</P>
<P>
Nationwide daily distribution of petrol is over 150,000 gallons
(681,900 liters) and diesel oil over 400,000 gallons (1.818
million liters).  
</P>
