<HEADLINE> Chinese Athletes Take 35 Medals at World Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese athletes won one
gold, one silver and two bronzes in the acrobatic gymnastics at
the World Games in Lahti on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Li Renjie and Song Min won the gold medal on 29.83 points in
the men's double acrobatics while athletes from Britain and Poland
took the silver and bronze respectively.
</P>
<P>
The mixed double title went to Russia with 29.88 points while
China finished in the second place by a slim margin of 0.03.
</P>
<P>
Russia reapt its harvest of four gold medals from the women's
double, triple, men's quartet and mixed double in the acrobatic
gymnastics.
</P>
<P>
In the other finals of the day, Vladimir Ignatenkov of Russia
won the gold medal with 87.89 points in the men's tumbling while
the women's title was won by Olena Chabanenko of Ukraine on 76.90
points.
</P>
<P>
Nikolai Kazak of Belarus and Elena Saveleva took the titles of
the men's and women's trampolining.
</P>
<P>
Eric Andresson of Sweden claimed the men's figure skating
crown, followed by Clemente Cerezo of Spain and Lee Taylor of
Britain.
</P>
<P>
Australian Tammy Briant triumphed in the women's figure skating
finals while American Jennifer Orcutt and French Laure Bourguignon
placed second and third.
</P>
<P>
The Germans and two American pairs took the top three spots in
the double-dancing skating.
</P>
<P>
So far, the Chinese athletes have accumulated a total of 35
medals including 17 golds as their competitive sports were all
concluded. 
</P>
