<HEADLINE> Thailand to Issue New Banknotes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Thailand will begin
to issue 100 million new 50-baht banknotes to replace the old
ones, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The old 50-baht banknote has been in circulation for 12 years
and is becoming easier to be forged, the Thai central bank said.
</P>
<P>
The new banknote will feature the royal image of Thai King
Bhumibol Adulyadej imprinted on dark blue polymer base, which will
last three times longer than the existing banknotes made of paper.
</P>
<P>
The new banknote will initially be produced in Australia before
the Thai central bank starts to print it at home next year.
</P>
<P>
The central bank said that if it is successful with the
issuance of the new 50-baht banknotes, it might print banknotes
with different values.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it said, the old 50-baht banknotes will remain in
use until the central bank collects around 148 million of them.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
