<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Thailand exported 2.3 million
tons of tapioca during the first five months of this year, down
5.4 percent compared with the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The export value of tapioca during the months totaled 8.2
billion baht (328 million U.S. dollars), down 21.4 percent,
according to statistics by the Thai Commerce Ministry available
today.
</P>
