<HEADLINE> Assets of China's Financial Institutions Expanding Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- China's financial industry has
developed steadily in tandem with the country's reform effort, Dai
Xianglong, governor of the People's Bank of China, the central
bank, said at a press conference today.
</P>
<P>
Dai revealed that total assets of all types of Chinese
financial institutions reached 13.28 trillion yuan (1.6 trillion
US dollars) by the end of June, which was 680 billion yuan (81.9
billion US dollars) more than at the beginning of this year and 10
trillion yuan (1.2 trillion US dollars) more than in 1990.
</P>
<P>
He added that between 1990 and 1996 the aggregate assets of all
financial institutions grew at an annual average of 24.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
"The financial sector is playing an increasingly important role
in strengthening macro-economic adjustment and supporting the
development of the national economy," Dai said. 
</P>
