<HEADLINE> Bank Lending Meets Needs of Economic Development, Says Governor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Increased lending has basically
met the requirements of economic development in China this year,
Dai Xianglong, governor of the People's Bank of China, said at a
press conference today.
</P>
<P>
The outstanding loan balance of all financial institutions
reached 6,870 billion yuan by the end of July, a rise of 450.3
billion yuan over that at the beginning of this year. The growth
was 15.6 billion yuan less over the same period of last year, Dai
said.
</P>
<P>
Of the total lending, 287.8 billion yuan was made by the
state-owned banks, 24.6 billion yuan less than a year ago.
</P>
<P>
At the end of July, the combined deposits of all financial
institutions totaled 7,610 billion yuan, of which enterprise
deposits reached 2,573.3 billion yuan, an increase of 25.6 percent
over the same period of last year.  
