<HEADLINE> 556 Crimes Committed Daily in Mexico City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 13 (Xinhua) -- About 83,370 crimes were
committed in this capital during the first six months of 1997,
raising the average daily offenses in the city to 556, said a
latest study by the Federal Districts Attorney Office.
</P>
<P>
Illegal acts here have been on the rise in recent years, which
rose from 141,000 in 1994 to 210,000 in 1995 and 240,000 in 1996,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Of the criminal acts committed in the first half of 1997,
violent robberies took the lion's share with 27,035 cases,
followed by assaults to pedestrians with 9,730 and robberies to
trucks with 7,677.
</P>
<P>
The criminal acts mainly took place in 11 neighborhoods of the
city, the study said. 
</P>
