<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China To Charge Foreign Tourists Same as Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- Foreign tourists will be charged
the same as domestic tourists for admission tickets to all tourist
attractions across China, according to a report in today's "China
Daily."
</P>
<P>
Some major sightseeing spots in Beijing City and Shaanxi and
Guangdong provinces have taken the lead in abandoning the old
practice of charging foreigners more than domestic visitors, it
said.
</P>
<P>
In Beijing, a single price for both domestic and overseas
visitors was introduced last week in some of its major tourist
attractions, such as the Great Wall and the Summer Palace.
</P>
<P>
For example, the unified ticket price of the most popular
section of the Great Wall in Badaling, north Beijing, is 25 yuan
(three dollars). The old prices were 15 yuan for domestic visitors
and 30 yuan for foreigners.
</P>
<P>
Despite some Chinese tourists' complaints about the raised
prices, many foreigners interviewed were happy with the unified
admission prices, according to the newspaper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
