<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over One Thousand Migrants Died on Mexico-U.S. Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 13 (Xinhua) -- At least 1,185 illegal
migrants died in the last four months along the border between
Mexico and the United States, a study released today shows.
</P>
<P>
The study carried out by Houston University, with the
participation of Mexican analysts, shows 72 percent of the those
who died were drowned in the border river Rio Grande while 16
percent died in railroad overridings and dehydration.
</P>
<P>
The study does not include those "invisible" deaths, in which
the bodies can not be retrieved or registered.
</P>
<P>
Though the study gives no details of the victims, experts
consider most are males between 18 to 29 years old, coming mainly
from Mexico and Central America. 
</P>
</TEXT>
