<HEADLINE> Argentina to Establish Mendoza Free Trade Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Argentina will establish a
free trade zone in the province of Mendoza to promote the
development of foreign trade, particularly with Chile.
</P>
<P>
A contract for the project was signed today by the Mendoza
government and the private firm that acquired the public bidding
for the task.
</P>
<P>
According to government sources, the 150-hectare free trade
zone will be located in the department of Lujan de Cuyo, 18
kilometers south Mendoza City, the provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
The consortium in charge of the project must finish the the
construction of roads and buildings needed in 10 months. The
buildings will house the customs office, the administrative
authorities and warehouses.
</P>
<P>
The free trade zone will be side by side with an existing
industrial park in the region, so some facilities are available at
present. 
