<HEADLINE> Brazil, Argentina Boost Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Bilateral trade between
Brazil and Argentina increased by 30 percent to 6.8 billion
U.S. dollars in the first half of 1997 compared with the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's official statistics revealed that during the first six
months of this year, Argentine exports to Brazil amounted to 3.9
billion dollars, while Brazil suffered a 1 billion dollar deficit
with its 2.9 billion dollar exports to Argentina.
</P>
<P>
Brazil diversified and increased the number of products
imported from Argentina from 270 to 311 items.
</P>
<P>
Argentina's car sales to Brazil doubled, truck and bus sales
rose by 108 percent, while sales of automobile parts increased by
10 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Brazilian exports of wheat, cotton and powdered milk
showed a downward trend. 
</P>
