<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 100,000 People Die of Heart Diseases in Argentina Annually </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 13 (Xinhua) -- About 100,000 people die
annually in Argentina due to heart-related problems, the Argentine
Cardiology Fund (FCA) said in a statement released to the press
today.
</P>
<P>
FCA chairman Saul Drajer said heart diseases are the main death
cause and account for 50 percent of the country's casualties.
</P>
<P>
In order to control the incidence of heart attacks, the FCA
launched a prevention media campaign aiming at fighting risk
factors for cardiovascular diseases.
</P>
<P>
The campaign includes the broadcasting of messages encouraging
physical duties like exercises, health food and outdoor activities.
</P>
<P>
The FCA expects to teach common citizens to provide first aid
to handle eventual emergencies regarding heart attacks.
</P>
<P>
More than 70,000 volunteers have been trained for the task.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
