Speaking on a local TV channel, Kruglov said the central
government is likely to offer the Pontic Navy Yard of the city a
contract to construct 16 all-container ships and bulk cargo
carriers.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said, the government has promised to grant
credits to the State Committee for Fisheries to buy two 5,500-ton
fishing trawlers from the Pontic Navy Yard.
</P>
<P>
Another major manufacturer of the city, the Ocean Shipyard, is
also likely to win a contract to build a large carrier for the
Black Sea Shipping Company, Kruglov added.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the Ukrainian shipbuilding industry slipped
into a crisis due to economic hardship and lack of orders from
domestic companies.
</P>
<P>
Producers who cannot adjust to the market economy and stiff
international competition made the situation worse.
</P>
<P>
The Ukrainian cabinet, meeting last Wednesday, considered
writing off the sector's financial obligations to help it tide
over the difficulties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
