<HEADLINE> China's Foreign Exchange Reserves Hit 126 Billion US Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 14 (Xinhua) -- China's foreign exchange
reserves reached 126 billion US dollars by the end of July, an
increase of 21 billion US dollars from the beginning of this year,
Dai Xianglong, governor of the People's Bank of China, said at a
press conference today.
</P>
<P>
Dai also said that the exchange rate of the Chinese currency,
the Renminbi (RMB) yuan, has largely been at the stable level of
8.29 against the US dollar this year.
</P>
<P>
The real exchange rate of the RMB has experienced a certain
range of appreciation owing to price decreases in the country, he
said.  
</P>
