<HEADLINE> World's Smallest Monkey Found in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, August 13 (Xinhua) -- A new species of monkey,
the smallest in the world with the size of a mouse, has been
discovered in the Amazon region in Brazil, the local media
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Danish biologist Mark Van Roosmalen, who spotted such monkeys
11 years ago when working in the region, captured one last April.
</P>
<P>
The monkeys, weighing between 160 and 200 grams, live in groups
of 30 in an area of about 3 million hectares in the Amazon region,
Roosmalen was quoted as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
