<DOCNO> XIE19970814.0276 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank Indonesia Intervenes in Currency Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 14 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian currency of
rupiah plummeted to a record low against the U.S. dollar
Wednesday, promoting the central bank to intervene in the market.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah hit the weak end of the intervention band at 2,682
rupiah but recovered to 2,615 rupiah after Bank Indonesia sold an
estimated 500 million U.S. dollars. But the rupiah slipped back to
close at 2,645/05.
</P>
<P>
Early Wednesday morning, Bank Indonesia raised overnight
interest rates to 15 percent, while one week rate was raised to
10.5 percent, two weeks to 11 percent, one month to 11.625
percent, six months to 12.125 percent and one year to 12.75
percent.
</P>
<P>
The interest rates hike is likely to result in a further
tightening of liquidity in the next few days, analysts said.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the pressure on the rupiah was not driven by
internal factor, but is "still a spillover from regional
economies."
</P>
<P>
They said the volatility of the rupiah has not reached its
peak. Therefore it is necessary to keep a close eye on regional
factors.
</P>
<P>
Rupiah fluctuation began on July 11 after Bank Indonesia
enlarging spread of rupiah exchange rate from 8 percent to 12
percent. The lowest plunge took place on July 21 when rupiah
dropped to 2,660 per U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the finance minister, the Bank Indonesia governor
and the information minister Wednesday asked the press to help
reduce the adverse effects on the Indonesian economy caused by the
monetary condition.
</P>
<P>
They felt that the media played a significant role in
overcoming the effects, because the negative consequences to the
money market and the stock exchange were often caused by media
reports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970814.0277 </DOCNO>
