<HEADLINE> Venezuela's Unemployment Rate Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela's unemployment rate
dropped 0.3 percentage point to 12.1 percent in the first six
months of 1997 from the same period of 1996, the Central Office of
Information and Statistics (OCEI) said today.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate fall resulted in 13,117 more jobs, it said.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment rate of the building industry, down by 0.1
percent, is now the highest, amounting to 20.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela's labor market now boasts a total of 9.18 million
people, the OCEI said.  
</P>
